Bookkeeper

View all jobs
Auckland CBD, Auckland
Bookkeeping & Small Practice Accounting (Accounting)
Full time
Add expected salary to your profile for insights
Posted 17d ago
Quick apply

About Us:

Cash Converters is a global leader in pre-loved goods and financial solutions, helping people unlock value, embrace sustainable shopping, and access financial support. Join our Support Office in the vibrant Commercial Bay area and become part of a dynamic, supportive team that values professionalism and teamwork. Whether you're looking for a stable, purpose-driven career or a stepping stone into the world of accounting, Cash Converters is the place for you!

 

So, whats involved?

You will join an in-house finance team to provide bookkeeping and related business services to our NZ Cash Converters business. Your primary duties will include: 

  • Banking Functions: Handle data retrieval, payments, collections, and allocations.
  • Reconciliations: Perform bank account and operating system reconciliations within our General Ledger software.
  • Financial Reporting: Assist in preparing monthly and quarterly management accounts.
  • Performance Analysis: Prepare and deliver weekly & monthly performance reports, including graphs and summaries.
  • Administrative Support: Perform general office duties as needed.

 

Youll likely have: 

  • A positive, can do attitude and fantastic attention to detail 
  • A disciplined approach to process 
  • Some bookkeeping experience or completed studies in the field.
  • Familiarity with accounting software and terminology
  • Microsoft Office Suite with moderate to high Excel competency 

 

Whats in It for You?

  • A rewarding, stable career with a global company and supportive team.
  • Access to great discounts across our stores and other top retailers.
  • Rewards and recognition for achieving milestones with the company.
  • Wellness packageincluding free flu vaccinations and doctor visits.
  • Enjoy fun team outings and celebrations.

 

 If you like what youve read, apply todaywed love to chat!
